modules.description: Provides functions for manipulating JavaScript objects and arrays, including conversion between OCaml and JS types, and methods for handling DOM elements. Works with OCaml's `Js.t` type and JavaScript-specific data structures. Used to extend functionality for custom DOM event handling and interop with third-party JS libraries.

provides a set of utility functions and type definitions for working with JavaScript objects in OCaml, focusing on safe and efficient interactions. It includes operations for creating, accessing, and manipulating JavaScript values, along with type-safe wrappers for common operations. Users can construct and deconstruct JavaScript objects, handle optional fields, and manage type conversions. For example, it enables the creation of JavaScript arrays from OCaml lists or the extraction of properties from JavaScript objects into OCaml records.
